Here is a visual prototype code (HTML/CSS/JS) that demonstrates the UI/UX design for the Phone Swap Request Feature:

**index.html**
```html
<!-- Main phone list page -->
<div class="phone-list-page">
  <h1>Phone List</h1>
  <button id="request-phone-swap-btn">Request Phone Swap</button>
  <div id="phone-modal" class="modal">
    <header>
      <h2>Request Phone Swap</h2>
    </header>
    <form id="phone-swap-form">
      <!-- Phone to Request dropdown -->
      <label for="phone-to-request">Phone to Request:</label>
      <select id="phone-to-request" name="phone-to-request"></select>

      <!-- Phone to Exchange dropdown -->
      <label for="phone-to-exchange">Phone to Exchange:</label>
      <select id="phone-to-exchange" name="phone-to-exchange"></select>

      <!-- Reason for Request text area (optional) -->
      <label for="reason-for-request">Reason for Request:</label>
      <textarea id="reason-for-request" name="reason-for-request"></textarea>

      <!-- Actions buttons -->
      <button type="submit">Submit Request</button>
      <button type="cancel">Cancel</button>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>
```
**styles.css**
```css
/* Global styles */

.phone-list-page {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
}

#phone-modal {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100vh;
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  display: none;
}

#phone-modal.active {
  display: block;
}

.modal-header {
  padding: 1rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
}

.modal-body {
  padding: 1rem;
}

.modal-footer {
  padding: 1rem;
  text-align: right;
}
```
**script.js**
```javascript
// Get the phone list page elements
const phoneListPage = document.getElementById('phone-list-page');
const requestPhoneSwapBtn = document.getElementById('request-phone-swap-btn');
const phoneModal = document.getElementById('phone-modal');

// Add event listener to the button
requestPhoneSwapBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
  // Toggle the modal visibility
  phoneModal.classList.toggle('active');
});

// Get the form elements
const phoneSwapForm = document.getElementById('phone-swap-form');
const phoneToRequestSelect = document.getElementById('phone-to-request');
const phoneToExchangeSelect = document.getElementById('phone-to-exchange');
const reasonForRequestTextarea = document.getElementById('reason-for-request');

// Add event listener to the submit button
phoneSwapForm.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  // Submit the form data to the API endpoint
  const formData = new FormData(phoneSwapForm);
  fetch('/api/phone-swaps', { method: 'POST', body: formData })
    .then((response) => response.json())
    .then((data) => {
      console.log(data);
      // Close the modal and display a confirmation message
      phoneModal.classList.remove('active');
      const confirmationMessage = document.createElement('p');
      confirmationMessage.textContent = `Phone swap request submitted successfully!`;
      phoneListPage.appendChild(confirmationMessage);
    })
    .catch((error) => {
      console.error(error);
      // Display an error message if the submission fails
      const errorMessage = document.createElement('p');
      errorMessage.textContent = `Error submitting phone swap request: ${error.message}`;
      phoneListPage.appendChild(errorMessage);
    });
});
```
This visual prototype code includes:

1. A main phone list page with a button to trigger the modal.
2. A modal popup with a form containing three fields: Phone to Request, Phone to Exchange, and Reason for Request (optional).
3. Actions buttons: Submit Request and Cancel.
4. JavaScript code to handle the form submission and API endpoint call.

Note that this is just a basic implementation, and you may need to modify it based on your specific requirements and project context.
